ations during their declining days. Beckeld gives a framework for why today's society is so fragmented and self-critical. He demonstrates that oikophobia is the antithesis of xenophobia. By this definition, the riots and civil unrest in the summer of 2020 were an expression of oikophobia. Excessive political correctness that attacks tradition and history is an expression of oikophobia. Beckeld argues that if we are to understand these behaviors and attitudes, we must understand oikophobia as a socio-historical phenomenon.Western Self-Contempt is a systematic analysis of oikophobia, combining political philosophy and history to examine how Western civilizations and cultures evolve from naïve and self-promoting beginnings to a state of self-loathing and decline. Concluding with a philosophical portrait of an increasingly interconnected Western civilization, Beckeld reveals how past events and philosophies, both in the US and in Europe, have led to a modern culture of self-questioning and self-rejection.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aCivilization, WesternxPolitical aspectsxHistory. 0aPolitical culturezWestern countriesxHistory. 0aSocial valueszWestern countriesxHistory. 4aHistory. 4aPhilosophy. 4aPolitical Theory. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh  aopposite of xenophobia, cultural self-hatred, decline of civilization.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311075182608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022 Englishz978311099276208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Phil